Could do the following which avoid calling TabletFileUtil.getVolumeFromFullPath.   This method converts a path to a string internally and then back to a path.  The following code uses the exisitng path object.
  Path tablePath = Objects.requireNonNull(tableIdPath.getParent(), "Table" + errorMsg);
  Preconditions.checkArgument(tablePath.getName().equals(Constants.HDFS_TABLES_DIR));
  Path volumePath = Objects.requireNonNull(tablePath.getParent());
When profiling in the past I have seen the Hadoop Path object show up.  So if its easy to avoid creating one, I try to do that.  This code would be used pretty frequently.

